    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - DISASSEMBLE - SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="2">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Cover the synchronizer assembly with a shop rag to prevent losing the three (3) springs under
                    pressure from the HI range synchronizer pin locations.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the larger LO range synchronizer ring on the bench (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b3">Figure 113</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b3" filename="../figg13/G13007B3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 113. Pull HI Range Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Grab both sides of the HI range synchronizer and pull (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b3">Figure 113</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the sliding clutch from the synchronizer ring LO range pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13007b4">Figure 114</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13007b4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13007b4" filename="../figg13/G13007B4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 114. Remove Sliding Clutch From Synchronizer Ring LO Range Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
